messages.content: What is the purpose of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree?
ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree is a custom node for ComfyUI that allows users to plug more stuff into the original String Function from ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts.
Who is credited for the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts?
All credits for the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts go to pythongosssss.
What should users do before installing the customized version of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree?
Users should first install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts before proceeding with the installation of the customized version of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree.
How can users install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts?

To install the original ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts, users need to open a terminal, navigate to the 'ComfyUI/custom_nodes/' directory, and run the command: 'git clone https://github.com/pythongosssss/ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts.git'.
What is the installation process for the customized version of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree?
To install the customized version of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree, users need to run the command: 'git clone https://github.com/wolfden/ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree.git' and then restart ComfyUI.
Where will the repository be cloned during the installation of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree?
The repository will be cloned into the 'ComfyUI/custom_nodes/' directory during the installation of ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree.
What should users expect after restarting ComfyUI and installing ComfyUi_String_Function_Tree?
After restarting ComfyUI, users should see a new menu under the utils submenu called String Function Tree. Clicking on it will make a new node appear in the workflow.
